{"title":"Ryder Innovation’s Luberetta lubes your chain without missing a link","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/01/eb21-ryder-innovations-luberetta-helps-lube-your-chain-without-missing-a-link/","date":1630516412000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270001\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Ryder Innovation, known for their Slug Plug tubeless repair kit and Nutcracker tool, has turned their attention to the messy affair of drivetrain maintenance. We spotted the Ryder Innovation Luberetta at EuroBike, a chain lube applicator that helps you apply chain lube exactly how the multitude of manufacturers recommend you do; one roller at a time. Let’s face it, most of us don’t have the time or, more accurately, the patience for that, so the Luberetta aims to make the process quick and painless.</p><h2>Ryder Innovations Luberetta</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x462/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"luberetta chain lube applicator applying yellow wax lube chain rollers\" width=\"1200\" height=\"711\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-297x176.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-800x474.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-120x71.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-768x455.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:780x462/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.7323921225499492\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-297x176.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-800x474.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-120x71.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130404/luberetta-yellow-wax-lube-application-drivetrain-lubrication-768x455.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\"></a></p><p>What is it? A patented silicone dispenser and chain guide attached to a lube canister that can be filled with up to 15ml of your favorite chain lube. You simply position the chain guide portion of the applicator onto the lower chain and squeeze the applicator to dispense lubricant as you back pedal to feed the chain through the applicator. As each roller passes through the chain guide, the silicone dispenser puts one drop of lube on each roller.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain.jpg\" alt=\"ryder luberetta applying lube drivetrain chain rollers underside view\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130410/ryder-luberetta-chain-lube-dispenser-finned-head-chain-768x512.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>That’s the theory, anyway. Of course, how hard you squeeze, and the viscosity of the lube you use, will determine just how much lube each roller gets. The idea is that the Luberetta applicator makes the process less messy and reduces waste. I guess I can see how that works; I usually just hover the lube bottle above the chain, squeezing as I back pedal, dropping one drop onto each roller as I go. I will occasionally miss a roller though, and end up with some lube on the floor, gone to waste. So yeah, I can see the potential here for more economical use of chain lube, which can be pretty expensive.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator.jpg\" alt=\"ryder innovation luberetta chain lube applicator head fins\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01130407/ryder-innovation-luberetta-chain-lube-applicator-768x576.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>The inside face of the Luberetta chain guide portion gets fins, which are said to help remove grime from the outer plates of the chain. A pin inside the cap prevents the dispenser clogging up with lube. If it does clog anyway, say if you’ve left the cap off for a period of time, you can pop it off easily, wash it with degreaser, then pop it back on again.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>Each Luberetta Chain Lube Applicator comes with two spare silicone dispensers and a one bottle of Ryder Innovations’ Wax Lube. We’re waiting on pricing info from Ryder.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.rydercycling.co.za/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>RyderInnovation.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8a78afdf0ddfac016b827f9af2db6393b6f4a91149c824a28f458864ea239548","category":"Cycling"}